WEBVTT

00:01.067 --> 00:02.667
So I'm thinking of going
to the beach,

00:02.669 --> 00:03.736
making a fresh start.

00:03.738 --> 00:06.671
This is gonna
be amazing.

00:06.673 --> 00:09.674
New town, new people,
a whole new me.

00:09.676 --> 00:10.943
Your place
looks amazing.

00:10.945 --> 00:13.211
It's my mother's.
It's her income property.

00:13.213 --> 00:15.614
She lives in Idaho,
so I just hand out the keys.

00:15.616 --> 00:17.282
I've been crashing
on the beach.

00:17.284 --> 00:18.350
You can stay here.

00:18.352 --> 00:19.818
-Who's your friend?
-Bodhi?

00:19.820 --> 00:21.553
He's so exotic.
[ Chuckles ]

00:21.555 --> 00:22.955
Introduce me.
But the new me.

00:22.957 --> 00:24.623
Remember,
Tickles is dead!

00:24.625 --> 00:27.025
How much does the baby
either look like

00:27.027 --> 00:28.961
or not look like the father
when it's born?

00:28.963 --> 00:32.665
Was the guy you had sex with
the same color as your fiancé?

00:34.168 --> 00:41.840
♪♪

00:41.842 --> 00:46.711
[ Birds chirping ]

00:46.713 --> 00:48.747
[ Children laughing ]

00:52.653 --> 00:54.252
Adam:<i>You have</i>
<i> a lovely beach home</i>

00:54.254 --> 00:56.521
<i> which I rented</i>
<i> for a family vacation.</i>

00:56.523 --> 00:58.190
<i> And I came prepared.</i>

00:58.192 --> 01:00.392
<i> I brought a random</i>
<i> quantity of sunscreen,</i>

01:00.394 --> 01:03.128
<i> an indiscriminate amount</i>
<i> of plastic cups for water,</i>

01:03.130 --> 01:05.129
<i> an unspecified number</i>
<i> of Cheez-Its,</i>

01:05.131 --> 01:07.065
<i> an arbitrary variety</i>
<i> of board games,</i>

01:07.067 --> 01:09.401
<i> and a hodgepodge</i>
<i> of karaoke CDs.</i>

01:09.403 --> 01:11.936
<i> My name is Adam,</i>
<i> and up until recently,</i>

01:11.938 --> 01:14.739
<i> I felt compelled</i>
<i> to count things.</i>

01:14.741 --> 01:17.676
<i> I grew up in a very ordinary</i>
<i> American home.</i>

01:17.678 --> 01:19.478
<i> But around the age of 8,</i>

01:19.480 --> 01:21.946
<i> I became less ordinary.</i>

01:21.948 --> 01:24.216
<i> I started counting...</i>
<i> everything.</i>

01:24.218 --> 01:26.885
<i> Something about it</i>
<i> made me happy.</i>

01:26.887 --> 01:32.157
♪♪

01:32.159 --> 01:33.625
<i> No matter what else</i>
<i> was going on...</i>

01:33.627 --> 01:36.028
Announcer: Capitals score!

01:36.030 --> 01:38.296
<i> ...I always found more joy</i>
<i> in counting.</i>

01:38.298 --> 01:39.431
<i> And because of that,</i>

01:39.433 --> 01:42.767
<i> I missed out on a lot</i>
<i> of family bonding.</i>

01:42.769 --> 01:44.302
<i> So much so, that lately</i>
[ Phone rings ]

01:44.304 --> 01:46.505
<i> I've started to think</i>
<i> my parents and my brother have</i>

01:46.507 --> 01:48.306
<i> stopped inviting me to things.</i>
Woman: Leave a message.
[ Beep ]

01:48.308 --> 01:50.108
Adam: [ On answering machine ]
Hey, guys, it's Adam.

01:50.110 --> 01:51.910
Just wondering if anyone
is up for hanging out.

01:51.912 --> 01:53.245
Maybe we could play Dominoes

01:53.247 --> 01:55.247
if I promise not to count
all the dots.

01:55.249 --> 01:56.314
I won't look down.

01:56.316 --> 01:57.582
You can just move my pieces

01:57.584 --> 01:58.717
and tell me if I'm winning.

01:58.719 --> 01:59.784
You guys there?

01:59.786 --> 02:01.520
Pick up if you're there.

02:01.522 --> 02:03.321
♪♪

02:03.323 --> 02:06.859
Okay. Well, I'll just wait
till you get home.

02:06.861 --> 02:10.195
One, two, three, four...

02:10.197 --> 02:12.464
<i> I always knew the counting</i>
<i> might prevent me</i>

02:12.466 --> 02:13.866
<i> from my career goals,</i>

02:13.868 --> 02:16.068
<i> making new friends,</i>
<i> or even finding love.</i>

02:16.070 --> 02:19.604
Hey, Adam.
This is a really cool place.

02:19.606 --> 02:21.940
What happened
to your food?

02:21.942 --> 02:26.144
♪♪

02:26.146 --> 02:28.346
<i> But it was the fear</i>
<i> of losing my family</i>

02:28.348 --> 02:31.083
<i> that finally made me</i>
<i> take a long look in the mirror.</i>

02:31.085 --> 02:33.952
<i> 343 seconds, to be exact.</i>

02:33.954 --> 02:35.287
<i> I tried drugs,</i>

02:35.289 --> 02:38.090
<i> but they just</i>
<i> made me count slower.</i>

02:38.092 --> 02:42.427
♪♪

02:42.429 --> 02:45.097
<i> I tried acupuncture.</i>

02:45.099 --> 02:47.632
<i> That just proved to be</i>
<i> too much of a temptation.</i>

02:47.634 --> 02:49.501
[ Quietly ] ...nine, ten,
eleven, twelve, thirteen...

02:49.503 --> 02:51.636
<i> I even borrowed</i>
<i> my neighbor's dog's collar</i>

02:51.638 --> 02:54.239
<i> for a little shock therapy.</i>

02:54.241 --> 03:00.713
♪♪

03:00.715 --> 03:01.846
[ Electricity crackles ]

03:01.848 --> 03:04.449
[ Groaning ]

03:04.451 --> 03:08.853
♪♪

03:08.855 --> 03:12.725
[ Electricity crackles ]

03:12.727 --> 03:14.726
<i> Eventually, I went</i>
<i> to see a therapist.</i>

03:14.728 --> 03:17.729
<i> And after several months</i>
<i> of crying in her crying chair,</i>

03:17.731 --> 03:21.133
<i> I finally had a breakthrough.</i>

03:21.135 --> 03:24.403
<i> And I couldn't wait to reveal</i>
<i> the new me to my family.</i>

03:24.405 --> 03:26.471
Bernice...
check it out.

03:26.473 --> 03:28.340
I just rented a beach house
for me and my family,

03:28.342 --> 03:31.009
and I didn't even count how many
clicks of the mouse it took me.

03:31.011 --> 03:32.144
The website even buffered,

03:32.146 --> 03:33.878
and I just sang quietly
to myself

03:33.880 --> 03:36.081
without counting the rotations
of the loading wheel.

03:36.083 --> 03:38.283
I heard you the first six times
you said it.

03:38.285 --> 03:39.551
Did I say it
that many times?

03:39.553 --> 03:41.954
Hmm.
I wasn't counting.

03:41.956 --> 03:44.489
Ooh.

03:44.491 --> 03:45.890
Oh, wow.

03:45.892 --> 03:47.559
Your nephew's
gonna love that.

03:47.561 --> 03:50.362
I sure hope it fits.
He wouldn't let me measure him.

03:50.364 --> 03:52.965
Huh.

03:52.967 --> 03:55.434
Here you go, man.
[ Coins rattle ]

03:55.436 --> 03:57.436
Take care.

03:57.438 --> 03:59.103
[ Sniffs ]

03:59.105 --> 04:01.173
I'm sorry. The keys have
gotta be here somewhere.

04:01.175 --> 04:02.841
I'm just a bit
out of sorts.

04:02.843 --> 04:04.777
My fiancée gave birth
last week,

04:04.779 --> 04:06.711
and I haven't really
been sleeping.

04:06.713 --> 04:09.181
I looked down. [ Sighs ]
I shouldn't have looked down.

04:09.183 --> 04:10.783
Ah, well,
not a problem.

04:10.785 --> 04:12.384
My family doesn't arrive
till the evening.

04:12.386 --> 04:14.186
Normally, I'd be counting
the seconds,

04:14.188 --> 04:15.187
but I'm cured.

04:15.189 --> 04:16.855
Hey, Vivian,
could you check and see

04:16.857 --> 04:18.457
if the keys to the beach house
are back there?

04:18.459 --> 04:20.993
Vivian: Okay!
[ Cellphone rings ]

04:20.995 --> 04:22.795
[ Cellphone clicks ]
Hello?

04:22.797 --> 04:24.329
We're not gonna be able
to make it.

04:24.331 --> 04:25.530
What's the matter?

04:25.532 --> 04:27.265
Look, if this is
about counting, I'm cured.

04:27.267 --> 04:29.001
Th-That's what I want
to show you guys.

04:29.003 --> 04:31.736
Plus, I got everybody's
favorite snacks and board games.

04:31.738 --> 04:33.672
And I even rented
a karaoke machine

04:33.674 --> 04:34.939
that syncs up
to cool lights,

04:34.941 --> 04:36.140
just like at
Aunt Jean's wedding.

04:36.142 --> 04:37.409
Remember that wedding?

04:37.411 --> 04:38.811
That's what I wanted to show you
with the karaoke.

04:38.813 --> 04:40.212
Adam, Adam, Adam.
The karaoke is --

04:40.214 --> 04:41.413
It sounds great,

04:41.415 --> 04:42.881
a-and I'm sure
you think you're cured,

04:42.883 --> 04:44.549
but yesterday,

04:44.551 --> 04:46.951
some moron drove their car
into the oil-changing pit,

04:46.953 --> 04:48.220
and I might have to go
to a funeral.

04:48.222 --> 04:49.822
Well, I-I could pick up
Mom and Dad.

04:49.824 --> 04:51.289
My car only has
one passenger seat,

04:51.291 --> 04:52.424
but I could
make two trips.

04:52.426 --> 04:54.559
And I know that sounds
like I'm counting,

04:54.561 --> 04:55.560
but I'm not.

04:55.562 --> 04:57.830
I'm just explaining.

04:57.832 --> 05:01.633
He wants to come pick you up,
one at a time.

05:01.635 --> 05:03.502
I think
we should go.

05:03.504 --> 05:06.771
Why, so we can watch him
count sand for a weekend?

05:06.773 --> 05:08.907
If Dave's not going,
I'm not going.

05:08.909 --> 05:10.509
Sorry, Adam.
It's just not gonna work out.

05:10.511 --> 05:12.377
We'll have
to reschedule.

05:12.379 --> 05:13.512
Okay.

05:13.514 --> 05:14.713
[ Cellphone beeps ]

05:14.715 --> 05:17.850
[ Cellphone beeps ]

05:17.852 --> 05:19.317
[ Sighing ] Oh.

05:19.319 --> 05:20.785
They were in my pocket
the whole time.

05:20.787 --> 05:22.855
[ Chuckles ]
Anyway, enjoy.

05:22.857 --> 05:23.856
[ Keys clank ]

05:23.858 --> 05:25.790
♪♪

05:25.792 --> 05:28.527
<i> So, it looks like I'm gonna</i>
<i> have a family vacation</i>

05:28.529 --> 05:29.794
<i> all by myself.</i>

05:29.796 --> 05:31.864
Hello.
You look like a local.

05:31.866 --> 05:35.600
A-Any tips on hot spots?

05:35.602 --> 05:38.270
Hello?

05:38.272 --> 05:39.938
Never mind.

05:39.940 --> 05:43.341
♪♪

05:43.343 --> 05:45.477
<i> I'm not gonna say</i>
<i> I'm not disappointed.</i>

05:45.479 --> 05:48.146
<i> I am.</i>

05:48.148 --> 05:49.748
<i> But I'm also worried.</i>

05:49.750 --> 05:52.684
<i> You see, part of my recovery</i>
<i> was revealing to my family</i>

05:52.686 --> 05:55.820
<i> what my big breakthrough was,</i>
<i> which wasn't gonna be easy.</i>

05:55.822 --> 05:58.156
<i> But up until now,</i>
<i> the excitement of doing so</i>

05:58.158 --> 05:59.691
<i> was keeping</i>
<i> the counting at bay.</i>

05:59.693 --> 06:01.426
<i> But suddenly,</i>
<i> I'm very aware of the fact</i>

06:01.428 --> 06:04.763
<i> that I've written</i>
<i> 23 A's, 14 K's, 13 T's</i>

06:04.765 --> 06:06.565
<i> in the last 46 seconds.</i>

06:06.567 --> 06:08.967
<i> Not to mention the 27 birds</i>
<i> that have flown overhead.</i>

06:08.969 --> 06:11.436
[ Bird caws ]
<i> 28 birds.</i>

06:11.438 --> 06:13.638
<i> And now I've written</i>
<i> the letter T 22 times.</i>

06:13.640 --> 06:15.240
<i> Actually, 32,</i>
<i> 'cause every time</i>

06:15.242 --> 06:16.508
<i> I write something,</i>
<i> it goes up.</i>

06:16.510 --> 06:17.642
<i> I'm up to 36.</i>

06:17.644 --> 06:18.711
<i> 39. 41.</i>

06:18.713 --> 06:20.579
<i> 42. 44.</i>

06:20.581 --> 06:21.313
[ Book thuds ]

06:25.217 --> 06:27.752
<i> The next day, the counting</i>
<i> was getting worse,</i>

06:27.754 --> 06:29.554
<i> and I couldn't just sit</i>
<i> in your house all day</i>

06:29.556 --> 06:31.890
<i> staring at 8 bottles</i>
<i> of sunscreen, 350 plastic cups,</i>

06:31.892 --> 06:34.359
<i> 1,846 Cheez-Its,</i>

06:34.361 --> 06:37.028
<i> 22 karaoke CDs,</i>
<i> and 12 board games,</i>

06:37.030 --> 06:39.564
<i> which have a total</i>
<i> of 811 pieces,</i>

06:39.566 --> 06:42.233
<i> so I decided</i>
<i> to venture out for lunch.</i>

06:42.235 --> 06:43.302
Just one?

06:43.304 --> 06:44.035
Always.

06:44.037 --> 06:45.304
Is the bar okay?

06:45.306 --> 06:46.571
Sure.

06:46.573 --> 06:49.274
Did you used to live up
in the mountains?

06:50.444 --> 06:53.512
Water, you said?
I'll be right back with that.

06:53.514 --> 06:55.447
<i> I was hoping that being</i>
<i> around some people</i>

06:55.449 --> 06:58.517
<i> would distract</i>
<i> from the counting.</i>

06:58.519 --> 07:00.585
<i> But even though I was</i>
<i> surrounded by people,</i>

07:00.587 --> 07:02.787
<i> I was still alone.</i>

07:02.789 --> 07:05.590
The bar's actually not okay.
May I sit at a table?

07:05.592 --> 07:08.927
♪♪

07:08.929 --> 07:13.064
♪♪

07:13.066 --> 07:15.066
One, two, three --
Can I get a booth?

07:15.068 --> 07:16.335
<i> I was spinning out of control,</i>

07:16.337 --> 07:17.736
<i> desperate for human</i>
<i> interaction.</i>

07:17.738 --> 07:19.004
I think you're wrong,
honey.

07:19.006 --> 07:20.339
I know for a fact
I'm right.

07:20.341 --> 07:22.073
I'd bet
my new knees on it.

07:22.075 --> 07:23.408
What's the name
of the woman

07:23.410 --> 07:24.943
Gary Hart cheated
on his wife with?

07:24.945 --> 07:26.145
Who's Gary Hart?

07:26.147 --> 07:27.879
Gary Hart was
the front runner

07:27.881 --> 07:29.881
of the Democratic nomination
in 1988,

07:29.883 --> 07:31.082
and her name was
Debbie Rowland.

07:31.084 --> 07:32.151
-No, it wasn't.
-Yes.

07:32.153 --> 07:34.085
Debbie Rowland was
my math teacher

07:34.087 --> 07:36.287
in the seventh grade.
Donna Rice!

07:36.289 --> 07:37.956
Rice.
[ Sighs ]

07:37.958 --> 07:39.558
Thank you, sir.

07:39.560 --> 07:40.692
Sure, anytime.

07:40.694 --> 07:42.494
I got a lot of info
in this old Google --

07:42.496 --> 07:43.562
noodle.

07:43.564 --> 07:46.431
[ All chuckle ]

07:46.433 --> 07:48.099
What's his name?

07:48.101 --> 07:49.901
This is Clark,
named after my uncle,

07:49.903 --> 07:52.437
who almost invented a cure
for psoriasis back in the '50s.

07:52.439 --> 07:54.439
Oh, he is so cute.

07:54.441 --> 07:55.640
And big.

07:55.642 --> 07:56.775
Ugh, tell me about it.

07:56.777 --> 07:59.178
He busted through my cooch
like the Kool-Aid Man.

07:59.180 --> 08:00.912
[ Imitating Kool-Aid Man ]
Oh, yeah?

08:00.914 --> 08:02.313
[ Laughs ]
Okay.

08:02.315 --> 08:03.782
I'm gonna go check my e-mails

08:03.784 --> 08:06.585
since somebody decided
to cancel the Internet at home

08:06.587 --> 08:08.119
because we have it
at work.

08:08.121 --> 08:09.320
You're lucky
I love you.

08:09.322 --> 08:11.056
Mm-hmm.
Love you, too.

08:11.058 --> 08:12.457
Just trying to save up
for our wedding.

08:12.459 --> 08:13.792
Can't afford to spend money
on things

08:13.794 --> 08:15.460
we could be getting
for free.

08:15.462 --> 08:16.795
You don't hear me complaining,
and I have to jerk off

08:16.797 --> 08:19.130
at the library...
theoretically.

08:19.132 --> 08:22.133
As soon as I get some sleep,
that's where I'm gonna go.

08:22.135 --> 08:24.469
Well, his first name
isn't "Captain."

08:24.471 --> 08:26.137
That's his rank
in the Navy.

08:26.139 --> 08:27.806
Actually,
Cap'n Crunch's full name

08:27.808 --> 08:30.742
is Horatio Magellan Crunch.

08:30.744 --> 08:32.343
<i> The thought</i>
<i> of making some friends</i>

08:32.345 --> 08:33.745
<i> started to distract me</i>
<i> from counting,</i>

08:33.747 --> 08:36.014
<i> so I decided</i>
<i> to step up my game.</i>

08:36.016 --> 08:37.348
Psst!

08:37.350 --> 08:40.586
Can I have three orders
of the onion ring towers?

08:42.355 --> 08:44.890
Hey, Tommy.
Can you put one of these up?

08:44.892 --> 08:46.625
Who's this?

08:46.627 --> 08:48.027
My buddy.

08:48.029 --> 08:49.761
He was smoking a joint
in my van,

08:49.763 --> 08:51.096
and when I came back,

08:51.098 --> 08:53.164
the van was burned,
and he was gone.

08:53.166 --> 08:54.966
I mean, I found
some bones in the ashes,

08:54.968 --> 08:56.501
but I'm really hoping

08:56.503 --> 08:58.437
that was from the chicken
I was eating the other night.

08:58.439 --> 09:00.772
It's hard to tell though,
you know.

09:00.774 --> 09:04.109
Eddie was a little guy,
and I did eat a whole bucket.

09:04.111 --> 09:06.711
I like the picture you drew --
very Picasso.

09:06.713 --> 09:10.515
Thanks.
Everyone keeps saying that.

09:10.517 --> 09:12.050
[ Hushed ] What does
"Picasso" mean?

09:12.052 --> 09:13.252
[ Camera shutter clicks ]

09:13.254 --> 09:14.453
I believe the actor
you're thinking of

09:14.455 --> 09:16.455
is named Bob Balaban.
Ooh!

09:16.457 --> 09:19.524
I did not expect there to be
this many onion rings.

09:19.526 --> 09:21.860
They look so much smaller
in the picture.

09:21.862 --> 09:23.328
I would hate to see
these puppies go to waste.

09:23.330 --> 09:24.529
You guys like
onion rings?

09:24.531 --> 09:25.664
Yeah.  No.
They're all right.

09:25.666 --> 09:27.132
Great.

09:27.134 --> 09:30.135
Probably be easier
to bring these over to you.

09:30.137 --> 09:31.670
♪♪

09:31.672 --> 09:34.473
Dig in, guys.

09:38.345 --> 09:39.544
Ah, someone
getting the jump

09:39.546 --> 09:40.879
on some early
Christmas shopping?

09:40.881 --> 09:42.547
[ Chuckles ]
Caught me.

09:42.549 --> 09:43.949
Don't forget.
We got a $15 limit.

09:43.951 --> 09:46.151
Plus, you've already given me
the best gift ever.

09:46.153 --> 09:47.486
[ Chuckling ]
Speaking of which,

09:47.488 --> 09:48.954
he smells like shit,
and we're out of diapers.

09:48.956 --> 09:50.956
Okay. Yep.
I'll be right out there.

09:50.958 --> 09:52.891
Okay, remember,
$15 limit.

09:52.893 --> 09:54.159
The challenge is
half the fun.

09:54.161 --> 09:55.894
[ Laughs ]

09:55.896 --> 09:57.629
[ Sighs ]

09:57.631 --> 09:59.230
So, it was supposed to be
a family vacation.

09:59.232 --> 10:00.565
It's a shame
they had to cancel.

10:00.567 --> 10:02.367
I brought a ton of food
and board games.

10:02.369 --> 10:04.103
All Lew brought was
a deck of cards.

10:04.105 --> 10:06.171
If I play Crazy Eights
one more time,

10:06.173 --> 10:08.707
<i> I'm</i>gonna go crazy.
[ Laughs ]

10:08.709 --> 10:10.241
That's hilarious.

10:10.243 --> 10:11.843
No, it's not.
Please don't encourage her.

10:11.845 --> 10:14.045
Look, you guys are letting me
crash your lunch.

10:14.047 --> 10:15.380
Can I get another
place setting?

10:15.382 --> 10:17.983
The least I could do is have you
over for game night.

10:17.985 --> 10:18.917
Sure.
Sure.

10:18.919 --> 10:20.119
[ Sucking teeth ]

10:20.121 --> 10:21.386
Did I get it?

10:21.388 --> 10:22.921
Nope, still there.
I'll get it.

10:22.923 --> 10:26.525
All right.

10:26.527 --> 10:27.993
Jesus.
How much stuff is in there?

10:27.995 --> 10:28.994
Mm!

10:28.996 --> 10:30.996
Ah! Got it.

10:30.998 --> 10:32.931
♪♪

10:32.933 --> 10:37.202
Anyone interested in splitting
the chicken pot pie?

